The start symbol is  

S → NT81 NT90  

so the entire string must split into two contiguous parts:  
• a substring generated by NT81  
• a single terminal generated by NT90  

NT90 has exactly one production: NT90 → 't14'.  
Therefore the last symbol of any string in the language must be t14.

The given string ends with t30, not t14, so no derivation from S is possible.

Hence the grammar cannot generate the string.
